hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 494<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(11/29/02 9:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Near-Earth Asteroid Explosions.</span><hr size=1> Edward Teller proposed for SDI an orbital X-ray laser that would detonate a nuclear bomb for it's X-ray source.  The weapon would consume itself as a big fireball in the process.  I think Teller makes most mad scientists look like innocent high school physics teachers.  I like that particular quality about him.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2637<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/1/02 9:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Near-Earth Asteroid Explosions.</span><hr size=1> That guy is a legend. What a mind. Him and Einstein could have had some interesting conversations.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1575<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/1/02 1:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Near-Earth Asteroid Explosions.</span><hr size=1> That sounds like the weapon system on the Orion in the book 'Footfall'. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2669<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/8/02 1:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Near-Earth Asteroid Explosions.</span><hr size=1> Forget about &quot;force fields&quot; saving your butt when atomic weaponry is taken to its full potential. We've hardly scratched the surface. As soon as a space military is established we can pretty much kiss World Wars goodbye. It should be relatively peaceful for awhile. Assuming only one nation makes that transition to Space based weaponry and it's a Western nation. I'm not so optimistic about a Chinese Super Power having that kind of power but I doubt the West will standby and do nothing as China advances its exploration program. <br>
<br>
Assuming they don't build an Orion secretly and surpass our capabilities completely overnight. By the time we caught up with that kind of achievement, they would probably already own the bulk of the solar system. They could even be capable of stopping us from leaving Earth altogether. All hail the new world regime or die fighting it. Not only could they stop ships leaving. They would soon have the in-space technology to stop nukes reaching China. But hey, China would never dream of building an Orion. Would they?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1617<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/8/02 7:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Near-Earth Asteroid Explosions.</span><hr size=1> Considering that China has yet to put a single person in space<br>
